{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The clause extractor identifies all key terms (parties, dates, obligations, penalties) present in the contract.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Failure boundary is model-output quality: extracting all key legal terms depends on real AI understanding of contract language, not just local parsing logic. A stubbed extractor would hide misses/false negatives, so Integration is insufficient. Rejected Workflow because this behavior is a single reviewer outcome, not a multi-agent sequence.","test_description":"Run the real clause-extractor model on a labeled contract set with gold key-term annotations; assert recall/precision thresholds for parties, dates, obligations, and penalties, and fail on missed required terms.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.78,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The risk assessor flags language that would be problematic under the configured risk policy, even when the problematic phrasing is indirect or euphemistic.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires semantic interpretation of indirect/euphemistic phrasing under policy, which is AI judgment quality. Deterministic mocks would trivially pass and miss real model failures. Rejected Workflow because only one reviewer’s decision quality is under test.","test_description":"Use real risk-assessor model calls on a curated corpus containing direct and euphemistic risky clauses mapped to expected policy outcomes; assert detection rate and acceptable false-positive bounds.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.86,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The compliance checker correctly determines whether the contract meets all applicable regulatory requirements for the configured jurisdiction.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This is correctness of AI compliance determination against jurisdictional requirements, so real model reasoning quality is the primary failure boundary. Integration tests can verify routing/config but not true compliance judgment accuracy. Rejected Workflow because this behavior covers one checker, not chained agentic steps.","test_description":"Execute the real compliance-checker on jurisdiction-labeled contracts with expert compliance ground truth; assert pass/fail decision accuracy and critical-requirement coverage for the configured jurisdiction.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.08}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When two reviewers flag the same clause with conflicting assessments (e.g., extractor says \"standard\" but risk assessor says \"high risk\"), the merge step preserves both assessments with attribution.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure appears at module handoff/merge boundary: outputs from separate reviewer modules must be reconciled without dropping either assessment or attribution. No real OS/network/subprocess is required (so not System), and no real model-quality dependence is required because crafted reviewer outputs can trigger the conflict path (so not Agentic). Rejected Workflow because behavior is merge conflict handling for provided reviewer results, not end-to-end multi-agent execution.","test_description":"Wire reviewer-output schemas from extractor and risk modules into the real merge component using conflicting clause cases; assert merged report retains both assessments with correct reviewer attribution and clause linkage.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full pipeline — dispatching to all three reviewers, collecting results, merging into a unified report — completes correctly for a real contract without losing any individual reviewer's findings.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This behavior is explicitly an end-to-end multi-step pipeline over three AI reviewers plus merge orchestration. Minimum real-failure boundary includes coordinating multiple agentic outputs; stubbing reviewers would hide loss/race/aggregation issues tied to real outputs and sequencing. Rejected lower levels because the behavior text requires full pipeline execution on a real contract with all reviewer findings preserved.","test_description":"Run the production-like pipeline on real contracts with all three real reviewers enabled in parallel; verify completion, presence of each reviewer’s findings in the final report, and no dropped/conflicted entries after merge.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.7}}]}
